						<summary>

						<p>On the north and east walls of the central shrine in the Āmalakēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja III (?) Year [·3]+1.</p>						

						<p>The portion containing the date is damaged. It is stated that the grant was made on some day in Paṅgūṉi.</p>						

						<p>This inscription seems to record a sale of land as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> to the temple of god Tirunellikkā-uḍaiyār, receiving 1000 <hi rend="italic">kāśus</hi>, by Śokki, wife of Tamiḻavēlāṉ of •••• ṭṭaiyanallūr who had Tillaināyakaṉ as her guardian and another woman whose identity is not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
